    <h2>U.S. Supreme Court</h2>
    <h1>Rush v. Parker, 9 U.S. 287 (1809)</h1>
    <h2>Rush v. Parker</h2>
    <h2>9 U.S. (5 Cranch) 287</h2>
    <h2>ERROR TO THE CIRCUIT COURT</h2>
    <h2>OF THE DISTRICT OF MARYLAND</h2>
    <h2>Syllabus</h2>
    <p>Held that this Court will give time to procure affidavits as to the value of the matter in dispute.</p>
    <n id="p288">288</n>
    <p>This being the last day of the term, and no affidavits having been produced, the writ of error was dismissed, this Court having no jurisdiction in the case.</p>
